es calculated as on Oct 31, 2013)</li>\r\n	<li>Cost of extension/deviation of air ticket</li>\r\n	<li>Standard hotel Check in Time : 1500 hrs , Check out time : 1100 hrs</li>\r\n	<li>Any other expenses of personal nature</li>\r\n	<li>Portages at hotels, airport and sea ports</li>\r\n	<li>Anything not mentioned in the cost inclusions</li>\r\n	<li>Any Increase in ROE (As of now Calculated at USD 01= INR 62/-)</li>\r\n	<li>Tips to the coach driver will be USD 3 per person per day, the same is mandatory, to be paid before departure</li>\r\n	<li>As hotels / Flights / Itinerary / Route are subject to change without notice, no compensation will be</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:.5in;">Paid for changes you may need to make in your domestic travel. Subject to RBI / GOI approval for</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:.5in;">BTQ Passengers.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>YOU GO TRIP holds the right to change the airline, routing of itinerary and travel date (any point of</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:.5in;">Time before the departure of the tour; alternate options will be advised incase this happens.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><u>Important Note</u></em></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>All Group Tours would be conducted with Min 20 pax.&nbsp; If the Group size is below 30 pax means, the Guest would be transferred to the next available Group.&nbsp; If they want to go on the given dates means, it would be treated as SIC (Seat in Coach) basis with additional supplement cost.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>We are not holding any confirmed seat in the flight and rooms.&nbsp; Flight seats and rooms are subject to availability.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '<p align="center"><strong><em><u>Daywise Itinerary</u></em></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><u>Day 01:</u></em> <strong>Arrive Melbourne &ndash; Transfer to the Hotel </strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Arrive Melbourne and transfer to Tune hotel, 609 Swanston Street, Carlton, VIC 3053. Check in time is after 2pm. Early check in is subject to availability. Rest of the day at leisure. Stroll along leafy Lygon Street and discover Little Italy &ndash; the place where Melbourne&#39;s famous cafe culture was born. The home of Melbourne&#39;s Italian culture, Melbourne&#39;s &#39;Little Italy&#39; buzzes day and night - there&#39;s a mix of outdoor dining, bars and traditional shops. Take an evening stroll along Lygon Street and enjoy a gelati or an exquisite Italian cake, or dine in one of the many Italian, Indian, Greek, and Turkish restaurants.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><u>Day 02:</u></em> <strong>Full Day Philip Island Tour</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Breakfast at hotel. We leave late morning for our tour of Philip Island.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><u>Churchill Island</u></em> Our tour heads south east to skirt Westernport Bay, noted for its mangroves and water birds.&nbsp; View French Island, a onetime penal colony.&nbsp; At Churchill Island you&rsquo;ll have the opportunity to meet wallabies/kangaroos.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><u>Phillip Island</u></em> San Remo fishing village is the gateway to Phillip Island, a major tourist resort and the home for unique wildlife. We&rsquo;ll take you around this small island of some 100 square kilometres with time at the township of Visit the Koala Conservation Centre where you can see koalas from tree top boardwalks and a stop at Seal Rocks where you&rsquo;ll have time to walk on the boardwalk overlooking the Nobbies.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><u>Penguin Parade</u></em> Witness the world phenomenon of the Penguin Parade. The Little Penguins return from the sea each evening at dusk after spending the day up to 100km off shore. Watch as they leave the sea, cross the beach and go to their burrows. Walk through the Visitor Centre&rsquo;s &ldquo;Penguin World&rdquo; and learn of the life of the Little Penguin. (Please bring warm waterproof clothing as nights can be cold on the island in any season).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><u>Day 03:</u></em> <strong>Melbourne City Tour</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Breakfast at the hotel. Today take an am city tour to get an overview of Melbourne. Melbourne is one of the world&#39;s most livable cities and a Melbourne City Tour will show you why.&nbsp; Enjoy the rich cultural vibe, the relaxed elegant charm and the cosmopolitan feel that Melbourne has to offer.&nbsp; This Melbourne Tour will allow you to explore architectural treasures, beautiful historical gardens and the thriving restaurants, cafes and markets. Rest of the afternoon free to shop at the DFO outlets or Harbourtown. You will visit the Eureka Sky deck for spectacular views over Melbourne and the thrilling Edge experience in the evening.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><u>Day 04:</u></em> <strong>Melbourne to Gold Coast &ndash; Transfer to Hotel</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Breakfast at hotel. Check out and transfer to the airport for your flight to the Gold Coast. Arrive Gold Coast and transfer to the Islander Resort, 3128 Surfers Paradise Blvd, Surfers Paradise, QLD 4217 for check in. Rest of the day at leisure. The world-famous Surfers Paradise beach and breathtaking skyline remains a major draw cards for millions of Gold Coast visitors each year. With the emergence of a fresh cultural scene, Surfers Paradise is thriving as a diverse cafe, restaurant, fashion and nightlife hub. Walk along the beach, explore the shopping and restaurants.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><u>Day 05:</u></em> <strong>Full Day Dream World Tour</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Breakfast at hotel. Transfer to Dreamworld theme Park by coach. Spend the whole day enjoying the rides and attractions at Dreamworld. Regarded as Australia&#39;s favourite family theme park, Dreamworld spans 30 hectares and is filled with a variety of rides, shows and attractions. So many worlds in one, Dreamworld is home to The Big 8 Thrill Rides including the Tower of Terror 2 - one of the world&#39;s tallest and fastest thrill ride, Pandamonium - a swinging rickshaw ride with a split personality, the Giant Drop with a freefall from 38 storeys or &#39;The Claw&#39; where you&#39;ll be propelled 9 storeys high, swinging up to 64kmh while spinning 360 degrees for a 90 second adrenalin rush. Enjoy Wiggles World, The Australian Wildlife Experience, Tiger Island - where magnificent and rare tigers interact with a team of dedicated tiger handlers, V8 Supercars Redine, and Australia&#39;s first Flow Rider - born from the roots of surfing, skateboarding and bodyboarding.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Return to the hotel by coach. Take a short walk to the Skypoint Observation Deck. SkyPoint located on top of the iconic Q1 Building, one of the world&#39;s tallest residential towers takes you to the highest point above the Gold Coast and offers spectacular 360 degree views from the surf to the hinterland and beyond. Rising 230m into the sky, SkyPoint is located on Level 77 &amp; 78 of the iconic Q1 Resort in southern Surfers Paradise. There are 9,463 curtain wall panels in the tower from level 3 to level 85(top of crown) which cover 32,685m2 and have a combined weight of 1,303 tonnes of glass and aluminium.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><u>Day 06:</u></em> <strong>Full Day Movie World Tour</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Breakfast at hotel. Transfer to Movie World. Spend the full day enjoying the rides and shows at the theme park. Park closes at 5pm. Return to hotel by coach.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><u>Warner Bros. Movie World</u></em> (more commonly referred to as Movie World) is a popular movie related theme park on the Gold Coast in Australia. It is owned and operated by Village Roadshow since the take over from Time Warner and is the only movie related park in Australia. It opened on 3 June 1991. The park contains various movie-themed rides and attractions ranging from motion simulators to roller coasters and slow river rides. In addition, costumed character performers also patrol the park, allowing visitors the chance to take photos with them. These include Batman, Austin Powers, Marilyn Monroe, Scooby Doo, The Mystery Inc. Gang and various Looney Tunes characters. Minor street shows including skits and singing performances are also present. The All-Star Parade showcases costumed characters alongside vehicles and movie-themed floats.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>There are a number of active film studios within the Movie World complex. House of Wax, the first Scooby Doo film, the 2003 Peter Pan film, Ghost Ship, The Condemned and Fortress are amongst the many films and television series produced at Warner Roadshow Studios, adjoining Warner Bros. Movie World. On 3 June 2011, Warner Bros. Movie World celebrated 20 years of being a theme park. Enjoy the thrilling roller coaster rides as well as the Hollywood stunt driver show and other attractions.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><u>Day 07:</u></em> <strong>Gold Coast to Sydney &ndash; Transfer to Hotel</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Breakfast at hotel. Check out time is 10am. You can check out and leave bags with the concierge. Spend the morning at leisure. Transfer to OOL airport by coach for your flight to Sydney. On arrival Sydney, transfer to The Great Southern Hotel, 717 George Street, Sydney NSW 2000.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><u>Day 08:</u></em> <strong>Sydney City Tour</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Breakfast at the hotel.Today take a morning tour of the city.&nbsp; Our tour travels via Darling Harbour and passing Sydney Entertainment Centre, Sydney Aquarium and Sydney Opera House.&nbsp; Tour through The Rocks - the birthplace of Sydney with its colourful and historic past.&nbsp; Other highlights include the Botanic Gardens, Parliament House, Hyde Park, Art Gallery and the Domain.&nbsp; Arrive at Mrs Macquaries Chair for a photo stop and witness the superb views of the city skyline, the Opera House, the Bridge and the Harbour.&nbsp; Sample the atmosphere as we drive through Kings Cross with its buskers, coffee shops and strip clubs. Following along the Harbour, we&#39;ll tour through Double Bay and Vaucluse, one of Sydney&#39;s most prominent suburbs.&nbsp; Continue on to The Gap for spectacular views of the Pacific Ocean. Bondi Beach is Australia&#39;s most famous surf beach.&nbsp; We&#39;ll take a break at Bondi and you&#39;ll have time to stroll along the beach front.&nbsp; Tour through Paddington on the way back to Sydney where you&#39;ll see Sydney Tower and Sydney Town Hall.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Afternoon at leisure. You can visit any 2 of the following 4 attractions: Aquarium, Madame Tussauds, Sydney Wildlife and the Sydney tower using a 2 attraction pass.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><u>Day 09:</u></em> <strong>Full Day Blue Mountains Tours</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Breakfast at the hotel. Today take a tour to the Blue Mountains. Enjoy a trip through the scenic Blue Mountains and admire the otherworldly beauty of the Jenolan Caves on a day tour from Sydney. Pass through the mountain township of Katoomba and take in panoramic views of the Three Sisters pinnacles at Echo Point. See the stalactites and dramatically lit chambers of the Jenolan Caves.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><u>Blue Mountains and the Three Sisters</u></em>: The Blue Mountains is a world heritage listed area of immense natural beauty.&nbsp; Covering over 248,000 hectares, the park is bigger than some countries!&nbsp; Massive deep valleys, narrow canyons, rainforests, waterfalls, rugged sandstone escarpments and craggy cliffs offer breathtaking vistas and experiences. Open every day of the year, award-winning Jenolan Caves is regarded as Australia&#39;s most outstanding cave system. With 11 spectacular show caves, underground rivers and awe-inspiring formations, Jenolan is among the finest and oldest cave systems in the world. Explore on fantastic guided cave tours. Reveal your wild side on Adventure Caving. Survive intriguing ghost tours and night tours. Experience live music underground. Try the self-guided Nettle Cave tour (11 languages, including Klingon).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Lucas Cave or Chifley Cave or Imperial Cave &ndash; any one tour is included. Above-ground, stroll through the glorious Aussie bush. Marvel at the impossibly Blue Lake. In the early morning or at dusk, glimpse native wildlife including kangaroos, wallabies and platypus.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><u>Day 10:</u></em> <strong>Departure. Transfer to the Airport</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Breakfast at hotel. Check out time is 10am. You can check out and store baggage at hotel (fee of AUD2 per bag applies for storage. Spend the day on your own exploring Chinatown, Paddys Market and the Haymarket area. Transfer to Sydney airport for your flight home.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>TOUR ENDS with HAPPY MEMORIES.</p>\r\n', '<p><strong><em><u>Cost :</u></em></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Rs.68,000/- + US$ 2250 = Rs.2,09,750/- Per Person on Twin Sharing</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Rs.68,000/- + US$ 2150 = Rs.2,03,450/- Per Person on Triple Sharing</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Rs.68,000/- + US$ 1650 = Rs.1,71,950/- Per Child (3 to 9 Years)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p align="center"><strong><em><u>If you Confirm before 20<sup>th</sup> Dec. 2013, following Discounts would apply</u></em></strong><br />\r\n<strong>3 Nights &amp; 4 Days Malaysia Package </strong><strong>(or)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p align="center"><strong>Cash Discount of Rs.20,000/- per Adult &amp; Rs.15,000/- per Child</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p align="center">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><u>Booking Terms</u></em></p>\r\n\r\n<p>To Confirm this booking, pls Send us the SCANNED COPY of ALL THE TRAVELING GUESTS (Pls see Minimum 6 Months Validity of Passport is required for any International Travel) to <a href="mailto:md@yougotrip.com">md@yougotrip.com</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>An Advance Payment of <strong>Rs.40,000/-</strong> (Non Refundable) in favo