(6, 'International Pack', 'ENCHANTING EUROPE (15 Nights & 16 Days) ', '<p align="center"><strong>ENCHANTING EUROPE (15 Nights &amp; 16 Days) </strong></p>\r\n', '<p><em><u>Inclusions :</u></em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>2 Nights Accommodation with Breakfast in JURYS INN Heathrow Hotel&nbsp; or similar in London</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>2 Nights Accommodation with Breakfast in NH HOTEL NAARDEN or similar in Netherlands</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>1 Night Accommodation with Breakfast in MERCURE HOTEL DREIEICH&nbsp; or similar in Germany</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>1 Night Accommodation with Breakfast in ALPHOTEL INNSBRUCK or similar in Austria</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>1 Night Accommodation with Breakfast in POINT HOTEL PIOVE or similar in Italy</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>3 Nights Accommodation with Breakfast in ALL WAYS GARDEN HOTEL &amp; LEISURE ROME or similar in Italy</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>3 Nights Accommodation with Breakfast in HOTEL WALDEGG or similar in Switzerland</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>2 Nights Accommodation with Breakfast in NOVOTEL ORLY RUNGIS PARIS or similar in France</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>15 Indian Dinners &amp; 15 lunches (hot or packed) &ndash; All meals in Europe </strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><u>SIGHTSEEING HIGHLIGHTS:</u></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><u>LONDON</u></em><strong> Orientation Tour, see Buckingham Palace, Trafalgar Square, Houses of Parliament, Madame Tussauds museum visit, Swaminarayan Temple</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><u>BRUSSELS</u></em><strong> Orientation Tour including the Grand Place, Mannekin Pis and Atomium (photo stop)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><u>THE NETHERLANDS</u></em><strong>&nbsp; Visit Zaanse Schans, Volendam and Madurodam Model Village or Keukenhof Gardens </strong><br />\r\n<em><u>COLOGNE</u></em><strong>&nbsp; Visit the Gothic Cathedral </strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><u>RHINE VALLEY</u></em><strong>&nbsp; Scenic drive and River Rhine Cruise</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><u>WATTENS</u></em><strong> Visit to Swarovski Crystal Worlds </strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><u>INNSBRUCK</u></em><strong>&nbsp; Orientation Tour including the Hofburg and Golden Roof</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><u>VERONA</u></em><strong> See Juliet&rsquo;s balcony and the Roman Arena</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><u>VENICE</u></em><strong> Boat ride to St. Mark&rsquo;s Square, visit St. Mark&rsquo;s Square - see the Bridge of Sighs, Doges Palace and the Basilica di San Marco </strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><u>FLORENCE</u></em><strong> View of the city from Piazzale Michelangelo and free time in historic centre of the city</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><u>ROME</u></em><strong> Guided City Tour including a visit to St. Peter&rsquo;s Basilica &amp; Vatican museum, see Piazza Venezia and the Roman Forum and Circus Maximus, Time Elevator show and Trevi Fountain </strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><u>PISA</u></em><strong>&nbsp; Visit Field of Miracles &ndash; see Cathedral, Baptistry and Leaning Tower</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><u>MILAN</u></em><strong> Free time in historic centre of the city</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><u>SWITZERLAND</u></em>: <strong>Cable car ride to Mount Titlis, visit to Lucerne and Interlaken, and train ride to Jungfraujoch - Top of Europe</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><u>PARIS</u></em><strong>: Paris City Tour: Orientation Tour of Paris, visit to the Gardens at the Palace of Versailles, third floor (**) of the Eiffel Tower, French Perfumery</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><u>Disneyland Paris Theme Park</u></em><strong>:&nbsp; Visit to Disneyland Paris &ndash; one day unlimited pass</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>All transportation by Luxury Executive coach with on board&nbsp; Air Cond. W.C, Video &amp; Audio</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>All tips, road tolls, and taxes throughout the tour</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Services of our English / Tamil Speaking Tour Guide / Manager</strong></p>\r\n', '<p><em><u>Package Excludes</u></em></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>UK Shenzhen visa fees of INR 16000/- per person</li>\r\n	<li>Indian GST at 3.09% on the total package</li>\r\n	<li>Any increase in the airfare, fuel surcharge taxes charged by the airlines (airfare &amp; taxes calculated as on Oct 31, 2013)</li>\r\n	<li>Cost of extension/deviation of air ticket</li>\r\n	<li>Standard hotel Check in Time : 1500 hrs , Check out time : 1100 hrs</li>\r\n	<li>Any other expenses of personal nature</li>\r\n	<li>Portages at hotels, airport and sea ports</li>\r\n	<li>Anything not mentioned in the cost inclusions</li>\r\n	<li>Any Increase in ROE (As of now Calculated at USD 01= INR 62/-)</li>\r\n	<li>Tips to the coach driver will be USD 3 per person per day, the same is mandatory, to be paid before departure</li>\r\n	<li>As hotels / Flights / Itinerary / Route are subject to change without notice, no compensation will be</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:.5in;">Paid for changes you may need to make in your domestic travel. Subject to RBI / GOI approval for</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:.5in;">BTQ Passengers.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>YOU GO TRIP holds the right to change the airline, routing of itinerary and travel date (any point of</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:.5in;">Time before the departure of the tour; alternate options will be advised incase this happens.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><u>Important Note</u></em></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>All Group Tours would be conducted with Min 30 pax.&nbsp; If the Group size is below 30 pax means, the Guest would be transferred to the next available Group.&nbsp; If they want to go on the given dates means, it would be treated as SIC (Seat in Coach) basis with additional supplement cost.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>We are not holding any confirmed seat in the flight and rooms.&nbsp; Flight seats and rooms are subject to availability.</p>\r\n', '<p align="center"><strong><em><u>Daywise Itinerary</u></em></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><u>Day 01:</u></em> <strong>Arrive in London. Transfer to the Hotel </strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Welcome to London and to the first day of your Grand Taj holidays Europe Tour! This afternoon at your LHR, meet your tour manager and proceed to hotel for check in.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><u>Day 02:</u></em> <strong>London Sightseeing</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>This morning , meet your tour manager and proceed with the London city tour, where we see the main sights: Buckingham Palace, Trafalgar Square, Big Ben, Westminster Abbey, the Houses of Parliament and the Tower Bridge.&nbsp; We also visit Madame Tussauds to see some of history&#39;s infamous wax works.&nbsp; Finally, we visit the Swaminarayan Temple &ndash; intricately designed and made of white Italian Carrara marble. Later we return to our&nbsp; hotel.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><u>Day 03:</u></em> <strong>London &ndash; Dover - Ferry &ndash; Calais &ndash; Brussels &ndash; The Netherlands</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Early morning, join the coach for a leisurely drive to Dover port, to board the ferry for the short channel crossing to Calais. Upon arrival, we proceed through Belgium.&nbsp; We first visit the city of Brussels, where on our orientation tour we see the Grand Place, the Mannekin Pis statue and the Atomium (photo stop).&nbsp; Later we drive to The Netherlands and check into our hotel for a two-night stay.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><u>Day 04:</u></em> <strong>The Netherlands: Zaanse Schans, Volendam, Amsterdam</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Today, we visit a working windmill village - Zaanse Schans. With its traditional green painted houses, warehouses and windmills the open air museum.&nbsp; Later, we visit a cheese and clog making farm and&nbsp; the picturesque village of Volendam. Continuing on, we visit the Madurodam Model Village to see miniature Holland (or Keukenhof Gardens for arrivals in Holland between March 21st and May 20th). After dinner, you may either rest at the hotel or join the Optional excursion - Amsterdam by Night Tour.&nbsp; We proceed for a canal cruise through the city&rsquo;s complex system of waterways.&nbsp; Later we return to our hotel.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><u>Day 05:</u></em> <strong>The Netherlands - Cologne &ndash; Rhine Cruise - Mannheim area</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Driving east across The Netherlands and into Germany, we join the autobahn and arrive at the famous city of Cologne where you can marvel Europe&rsquo;s largest Gothic twin spire cathedral.&nbsp; Continuing our drive into the Rhine valley we board a cruise ship for an unforgettable trip along the River Rhine.&nbsp; Admire the majestic views, mountain top fairy tale castles and ancient fortresses.&nbsp; Late evening check into our hotel.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><u>Day 06:</u></em> <strong>Mannheim area &ndash; Innsbruck</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Depart this morning for Austria.&nbsp; Our drive takes us through the region of the Bavarian Alps, arriving at Wattens, we visit Swarovski Crystal Worlds, for a tour through the kaleidoscope of senses and to see sparkling crystal artworks by famous artists.&nbsp; Visit the Crystal Worlds Shop displaying a unique selection of products.&nbsp; We then proceed to Innsbruck, the capital of the Tyrol region.&nbsp; Enjoy this charming town of green domes and red roofs - see the Hofburg and the Golden Roof.&nbsp; Later we check into our hotel for an overnight stay.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><u>Day 07:</u></em> <strong>Innsbruck &ndash; Verona - Padova area</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>This morning we drive across Europabrucke, one of Europe&rsquo;s highest bridges, admire the amazing views, winding our way through the Brenner pass we cross the Italian border.&nbsp; Welcome to Italy!&nbsp; Our first stop is to visit Shakespeare&#39;s Verona - see Juliet&#39;s balcony and the Roman Arena.&nbsp; We then drive to Venice, the city of unparalleled beauty and romantic gondolas.&nbsp; Our tour starts with a boat ride to St. Mark&rsquo;s Square &ndash; the most elegant square in the world, to see the Bridge of Sighs, the Doges Palace and the Basilica di San Marco.&nbsp; Late evening check into our hotel.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><u>Day 08:</u></em> <strong>Venice / Padova area &ndash; Florence &ndash; Rome</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Today we depart for Florence.&nbsp; We cross the Appennines and the gentle hilly countryside of Tuscany to reach Florence. On arrival, we will visit Piazzale Michelangelo to enjoy one of the best views of this renaissance city across the River Arno.&nbsp; You then have some free time to wander around this city, where traffic is banned from the historic centre, admiring its timeless beauty.&nbsp; Later we continue our journey to the &lsquo;Eternal City&rsquo;, where we check into our hotel for a two-night stay.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><u>Day 09:</u></em> <strong>Rome</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>This morning, we meet our local guide who will show us the splendours of St. Peter&rsquo;s Basilica and the Vatican Museums, including the Sistine Chapel, a renaissance masterpiece. Later, we take in other ancient sights &ndash; Piazza Venezia, the Roman Forum and Circus Maximus.&nbsp; Later experience The Time Elevator, created as a Time machine that allows you to travel back to 773 B.C. and to return to modern age through time travel.&nbsp; Starting with its foundation, through the glorious days of the ancient Roman empire, the Renaissance with its masterpieces of architecture and art, the events of the 20th century, culminating in an aerial flight over the Rome of today. Finally, we visit the spectacular Trevi Fountain, where you may make a wish.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><u>Day 10:</u></em> <strong>Rome &ndash; Pisa/ Florence area</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>This morning,&nbsp; we depart for Pisa, where we visit the Field of Miracles.&nbsp; Here you can marvel at the marble Cathedral in the Pisan Romanesque style, the Baptistery, and one of the wonders of the world, the legendary Leaning Tower.&nbsp; Late evening check into our hotel for an overnight stop.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><u>Day 11:</u></em> <strong>Florence area - Milan &ndash; Lugano area &ndash; Switzerland</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>After breakfast, we proceed to the fashion capital - Milan, here you have some time to explore the historic centre of the city &ndash; see the&nbsp; Duomo (Cathedral), La Scala Opera House and the Castello Sforzesco.&nbsp; Leaving Milan, we cross the Swiss border, passing spectacular scenery around the lake regions of Como and Lugano.&nbsp; We make a brief photo stop near Lake Lugano, before driving north through the Gotthard tunnel.&nbsp; We arrive at our hotel late evening, and check in for a three-night stay.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><u>Day 12:</u></em> <strong>Switzerland: Mount Titlis - Lucerne</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Driving through the Swiss alpine region and the winding mountain roads to the valley of Engelberg, we start our ascent to board the world&rsquo;s first revolving cable car, reaching the peak of 10,000 feet at Mount Titlis (weather permitting). Visit the Glacier Grotto or enjoy a breathtaking panorama from the sun terrace. In the afternoon, we begin our descent, passing melting glaciers and majestic waterfalls.&nbsp; Later we visit the town of Lucerne, to see the Chapel Bridge and the Lion Monument.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><u>Day 13:</u></em> <strong>Switzerland: Interlaken &ndash; Jungfraujoch</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Today, we first drive to the picturesque town of Interlaken, the scene of many &ldquo;Bollywood&rdquo; films, where you have some time to browse through the shops. From there a short drive brings us to Lauterbrunnen, where we board the train for the scenic journey to Jungfraujoch &ndash; Top of Europe, the highest railway station in Europe at 3,454 metres (weather permitting). Visit the Ice Palace with ice sculptures or enjoy the panoramic views from the Sphinx Terrace.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Early evening we begin our descent and return to our hotel.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&lsquo;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><u>Day 14:</u></em> <strong>Switzerland &ndash; Paris</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Early morning we leave the Swiss Alps behind us.&nbsp; Continue onto Paris, one of the most exciting and popular cities of Europe, renowned for it&rsquo;s fashion, perfumes, and of course - French champagne and wines. On arrival, we check into our hotel for a two nights stay. After dinner we proceed for River Seine Cruise &amp; Paris by Night Tour.&nbsp; Admire the spectacular facades from your covered boat. Later on our Paris by Night Tour we will see the main sights illuminated.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><u>Day 15:</u></em> <strong>Disneyland Theme Park</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Disneyland Paris Theme Park</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This morning we drive to the famous Disneyland Paris Theme Park where excitement awaits the entire family.&nbsp; Meet your favourite Disney characters, watch amazing shows, ride the hair-raising &ldquo;Space Mountain: Mission 2&rdquo; roller coaster, enter Indiana Jones and the Temple of Peril and find yourself in a runaway wagon speeding through the ancient ruins.&nbsp; After dinner you may either rest at the hotel or join us for an exciting optional Lido Paris Cabaret show. (Breakfast, Dinner)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><u>Day 16:</u></em> <strong>Paris City Tour - Departure. Transfer to the Airport</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>This morning, on our orientation tour of Paris, we will be introduced to the main sights of this beautiful city: Hotel des Invalides, Arc de Triomphe, Champs Elysees, Place de la Concorde, and the Opera.&nbsp; Later we proceed to Versailles, to visit the magnificent Gardens at the Palace of Versailles, the former residence of the famous &ldquo;Sun King&rdquo;. After Paris City Tour we will drop you in Paris Airport to your return flight to India.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>TOUR ENDS with HAPPY MEMORIES.</p>\r\n', '<p><em><u>Cost :</u></em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Rs.80,000/- + Euro 2,200 = Rs.2,69,200/- Per Person on Twin Sharing</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Rs.80,000/- + Euro 2,100 = Rs.2,60,600/- Per Person on Triple Sharing</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Rs.80,000/- + Euro 1,800 = Rs.2,34,800/- Per Child (3 to 9 Years)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p align="center">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p align="center"><strong><em><u>If you Confirm before 20<sup>th</sup> Dec. 2013, following Discounts would apply</u></em></strong><br />\r\n<strong>3 Nights &amp; 4 Days Srilanka Package</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p align="center"><strong>(or)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p align="center"><strong>Cash Discount of Rs.15,000/- per Adult &amp; Rs.10,000/- per Child</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><u>Booking Terms</u></em></p>\r\n\r\n<p>To Confirm this booking, pls Send us the SCANNED COPY of ALL THE TRAVELING GUESTS (Pls see Minimum 6 Months Validity of Passport is required for any International Travel) to <a href="mailto:md@yougotrip.com">md@yougotrip.com</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>An Advance Payment of <strong>Rs.40,000/-</strong> (Non Refundable) in favour of <strong>&ldquo;MILK WHITE HOSPITALITY SERVICES INDIA PVT LTD&rdquo;</strong> payable at Coimbatore or Transfer to the below Bank Account.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p align="center">Account Name:&rdquo;<strong>MILK WHITE HOSPITALITY SERVICES INDIA PRIVATE LIMITED&rdquo;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><u>ICICI BANK DETAILS</u>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <u>CANARA BANK DETAILS</u>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&n