>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Visit Epcot Center</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Enjoy Sea World </strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>City Tour of Miami</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Miami Biscayne Bay Cruise</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Enjoy City tour of Las Vegas </strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Visit Las Vegas Eiffel Tower </strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Enjoy City tour of San Francisco </strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Enjoy San Francisco Bay Cruise</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Enjoy San Francisco Cable Car Ride </strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Visit Santa Barbara </strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Enjoy Enjoy Famous &#39;17 Mile Drive&#39; </strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Enjoy City tour of Los Angeles </strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Enjoy Universal Studios</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>All Transfers in a A/c Coach with the Service of English Speaking Guide</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Cost of your Round Trip Economy Class Air ticket with airline taxes </strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Cost of your internal air tickets as per the itinerary.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Handling fee charged by the airlines for travel within USA one check - in baggage per person.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Porterage for 1 bag per person at all the hotels only.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Services of our English / Tamil Speaking Tour Guide / Manager</strong></p>\r\n', '<p><em><u>Package Excludes</u></em></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>US visa fees of INR 12000/- per person (US visa is subject to direct submission at the VFS interview by the passenger)</li>\r\n	<li>Indian GST at 3.09% on the total package</li>\r\n	<li>Any increase in the airfare, fuel surcharge taxes charged by the airlines (airfare &amp; taxes calculated as on Oct 31, 2013)</li>\r\n	<li>Cost of extension/deviation of air ticket</li>\r\n	<li>Standard hotel Check in Time : 1500 hrs , Check out time : 1100 hrs</li>\r\n	<li>Any other expenses of personal nature</li>\r\n	<li>Portages at hotels, airport and sea ports</li>\r\n	<li>Anything not mentioned in the cost inclusions</li>\r\n	<li>Any Increase in ROE (As of now Calculated at USD 01= INR 62/-)</li>\r\n	<li>Tips to the coach driver will be USD 3 per person per day, the same is mandatory, to be paid before departure</li>\r\n	<li>As hotels / Flights / Itinerary / Route are subject to change without notice, no compensation will be</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:.5in;">Paid for changes you may need to make in your domestic travel. Subject to RBI / GOI approval for</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:.5in;">BTQ Passengers.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>YOU GO TRIP holds the right to change the airline, routing of itinerary and travel date (any point of</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:.5in;">Time before the departure of the tour; alternate options will be advised incase this happens.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><u>Important Note</u></em></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>All Group Tours would be conducted with Min 30 pax.&nbsp; If the Group size is below 30 pax means, the Guest would be transferred to the next available Group.&nbsp; If they want to go on the given dates means, it would be treated as SIC (Seat in Coach) basis with additional supplement cost.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>We are not holding any confirmed seat in the flight and rooms.&nbsp; Flight seats and rooms are subject to availability.</p>\r\n', '<p align="center"><strong><em><u>Daywise Itinerary</u></em></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><u>Day 01:</u></em> <strong>Arrive in New York. Transfer to the Hotel </strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Welcome to the &quot;Big Apple,&quot; the &quot;City That Never Sleeps&quot;New York is a city of superlatives: America&#39;s biggest; its most exciting; its business and cultural capitals; the nation&#39;s trendsetter. For more than a century, it has been one of the world&#39;s major centers of commerce and finance. Upon arrival at the airport, you will be transferred to the hotel. Checkin to hotel. Overnight.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><u>Day 02:</u></em> <strong>City tour of New York with Top of the Rock, Statue of Liberty and Empire State building</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><u>City Tour of New York</u></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Begin by taking a ferry ride to Liberty Island to view the famous landmark, Statue of Liberty.&nbsp; Also see Financial District, Wall Street, Ground Zero &amp; City Hall.&nbsp; Later you will see Rockefeller Center, Central Park, Trump Towers, United Nations and more!&nbsp; Later in the day experience the view of a lifetime from the 86th floor of the Empire State Building and see some of the most impressive views of the city!</p>\r\n\r\n<p><u>Statue of Liberty</u> Designed by Frederic Barholdi and dedicated on October 28, 1886 as a gift from the People of France to the United States. &nbsp;This statue is an icon of freedom and of the United States and serves as a welcoming signal to immigrants arriving from around the world.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><u>Empire State Building</u> A 102-Story skyscraper, which is currently the city&rsquo;s tallest building.&nbsp; This is the site where the famous King Kong movie was shot.&nbsp; It&rsquo;s observation deck on the 86th floor is the best.&nbsp; Remember: Don&rsquo;t drop anything off the deck!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><u>Day 03:</u></em> <strong>Surface Transfer to Washington. Transfer to the Hotel</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Drive to Washington DC, capital of the United States of America. Guided tour to the Historic Neighborhoods and Monuments. Other than the federal government, tourism is DC&#39;s biggest industry. The city attracts almost twenty million visitors each year. After check-in at the hotel, spend some time for leisure. Overnight .</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><u>Day 04:</u></em> <strong>City Tour of Washington with Air and Space Museum</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><u>City Tour of Washington D.C.</u></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Today enjoy visits to U.S. Capitol Building, Washington Monument, Lincoln Memorial, Ford&#39;s Theater, Old Post Office, Union Station, Jefferson Memorial, Arlington Cemetery, Air and Space museum, The White House, National Cathedral, Georgetown, Embassy Row, Vietnam Memorial, Korean Memorial, FBI Building, National Archives...and much, much more!&nbsp; Also enjoy visit to the Smithsonian.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><u>Day 05:</u></em> <strong>Surface Transfer to the Niagara. Transfer to the Hotel</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Surface Transfer to Niagara to view the world famous falls, which forms one of the natural wonders of the World. We will board the famous boat &ldquo;Maid of the mist&rdquo; which takes us close to the thundering falls and around the American and Horseshoe Falls (seasonal). Return to the hotel. Overnight.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><u>Day 06:</u></em> <strong>Maid of the Mist. Fly to Orlando. Transfer to the Hotel</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Maid of the Mist: Boat tour of Niagara Falls, which starts at a calm part of the river, near the Rainbow Bridge, and takes passengers past the American and Bridal Veil Falls, then in to the dense mist of spray inside the curve of the Horseshoe Falls.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>After Maid of the Mist, today we depart to Orlando by flight. Orlando is the sixth largest city of Florida and is also known to be its largest inland city. The presence of Disney World theme park has made this city a well-known vacation spot. This city is said to welcome more than 52 million tourists every year. Upon arrival transfer to hotel. Overnight.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><u>Day 07:</u></em> <strong>Magic Kingdom</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><u>Magic Kingdom</u> Opened in 1971, It&#39;s been dubbed &quot;The Most Magical Place on Earth!&quot;, It is the place where storybook fantasy is everyday reality, and Disney classics are brought to life from the moment you step onto Main Street USA, you are transported to a place where the cares of the outside world seem to magically melt away.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><u>Day 08:</u></em> <strong>Epcot Center</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><u>Epcot Center</u> This theme park, opened in 1982, allows visitors to touch the future and travel the world with an amazing array of attractions and live performances. This is an area of 260 acres devoted to past achievements and the future of technology. World showcase offers a kind of permanent World Fair, with pavilions devoted to eleven countries.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><u>Day 09:</u></em> <strong>Sea World</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><u>Sea World Orlando</u> The world&#39;s largest Marine Park!&nbsp; Here you shall discover many attractions. We dare you to take a one-of-a kind water coaster thrill ride through the mysterious lost city of Atlantis. Soar through danger on a jet copter ride to the Wild Arctic. At Sea World, touch, feed or get face to face with awesome and amazing wild animals, including Shamu the dolphin and get in on all the action that draws you back again and again!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><u>Day 10:</u></em> <strong>Surface Transfer to Miami. City Tour of Miami with&nbsp;Biscayne&nbsp;Bay Cruise</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><u>City Tour of Miami</u></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Enjoy visits to Central Station/Bayfront Park, Ocean Drive, Lincoln Road, Collins Avenue &amp; 24th, Design District, Midtown Miami, Coconut Grove, Little Havana and much more.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><u>Biscayne Bay Cruise:</u>&nbsp;A short 75 minute boat ride over the waters of Miami&rsquo;s Biscayne Bay.&nbsp; See the most beautiful Real Estate and pristine skyline of the city.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><u>Day 11:</u></em> <strong>Miami &ndash; Board Norwegian Sky Cruise</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Morning spend your leisure time Miami. Evening Board the Norwegian Sky Cruise and enjoy next three days in the Cruise.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><u>Day 12:</u></em> <strong>Norwegian Sky Cruise &ndash; Nassau, Bahamas</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>From the waterfront to the end of Bay Street, you&#39;ll find some of the best duty-free shopping and a charming mix of architecture, both old and new. But there&#39;s plenty to do besides shopping - swim with the dolphins, try your luck in a casino or snorkel with colorful fish. View Shopping Guide (Current shopping maps available onboard.)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><u>Day 13:</u></em> <strong>Norwegian Sky Cruise &ndash; Great Stirrup Cay, Bahamas</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Spend a full day on the expanded white sandy beaches and enjoy the many activities we have to offer. Play in the water, go snorkel and see underwater delights, or get revved up on a waverunner adventure. The fun is endless here. Hungry? Grab a bite at our new 8,500-square foot beach buffet which includes a central pizza making station, two grills, hot and cold food stations, as well as fresh fruits and breads.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><u>Day 14:</u></em> <strong>Fly to Las Vegas. City tour of Las Vegas with Eiffel Tower. Transfer to the Hotel</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><u>City Tour of Las Vegas</u></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Enjoy a Night City Tour of Las Vegas, including Hotel Venetian and its unique architecture, Hotel Wynn, The Mirage Hotel, Hotel Bellagio, Bellagio Fountains, Golden Nugget, The &ldquo;Welcome to Las Vegas&rdquo; sign, History of Las Vegas and about the beautiful and one of kind hotels, Night view of the world famous Las Vegas Strip, Fremont Street &ndash; where over 12 million lights create a free show with pumping music.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><u>Day 15:</u></em> <strong>Grand Canyon</strong> (Optional Cost).</p>\r\n\r\n<p><u>GRAND CANYON</u> West Rim Bus Tour with Skywalk: On Arrival at the Canyon, enjoy a visit to the famous Skywalk; this transparent horseshoe-designed walkway around the edge of the Grand Canyon West Rim.&nbsp; See the spectacular views of the Canyons and don&rsquo;t forget to look below at the floor and see the depth of the canyon itself, which reaches thousands of feet below.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><u>Day 16:</u></em> <strong>Surface Transfer to San Francisco. City tour of San Francisco with Bay Cruise</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><u>City Tour of San Francisco</u></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Enjoy visits to Golden Gate Bridge, Fisherman&rsquo;s Wharf (includes Pier 39, Hyde Street Pier &amp; Ghirardelli Square), Lombard Street &ndash; The Craziest and Curviest Street in USA!&nbsp; Also see Marina District, Coastline Gorgeous Views of Forested Parklands and Upscale Neighborhoods, the Civic Centre, City Hall, Opera House, Financial District, Chinatown and more!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><u>Day 17:</u></em> <strong>Surface Transfer to Los Angeles. City tour of Los Angeles</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><u>City Tour of Los Angeles</u></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Proceed and drive though famous areas in this mecca city, including Sunset Blvd, Beverly Hills, The World Famous &ldquo;Hollywood&rdquo; Sign, The Hollywood Walk of Fame, TCL Chinese Theatre, Dolby Theatre, Grove Shopping Centre, Music Centre, Downtown Los Angeles, Hollywood Boulevard and more!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><u>Day 18: </u></em><strong>Universal Studios</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Universal Studios Hollywood: Relax in the comfort of a tram car as it takes you behind the scenes to show you how Hollywood makes movies.&nbsp; Enter &ldquo;Jurassic Park&rdquo;, where you will journey deep into the Jurassic Jungle.&nbsp; You will also experience the first-ever mega attraction based on the blockbuster TV Series, &ldquo;The Simpsons&rdquo;.&nbsp; This ride features the show&rsquo;s classic humor and many of its instantly famous and recognizable characters &ndash; all voiced by the original actors.&nbsp; Join Shrek, Donkey and Princess Fiona in &ldquo;Shrek 4D&rdquo;, an all-new adventure which picks up where the Oscar winning movie &ldquo;Shrek&rdquo; left off and puts you inside the action!&nbsp; Enjoy &ldquo;King Kong&rdquo; &ndash; the new attraction, where guests will wear special glasses as they enter a darkened sound stage aboard the Studio Tour trams and will be transported &ndash; via the magic of Surround Digital 4D projection &ndash; deep into the dark heart of the world of Skull Island.&nbsp; Also enjoy the newest rides&nbsp; &ldquo;Revenge of the Mummy&rdquo;, inspired by the acclaimed Hollywood blockbuster movie &ldquo;The Mummy&rdquo;.&nbsp; Take a terrifying journey through a real ancient Egyptian Tomb and be dazzled by this most exciting ride ever crated for a theme park.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><u>Day 19:</u></em> <strong>Departure. Transfer to the Airport</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>After breakfast, spend some time for leisure; proceed to board your flight to next destination.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><u>Day 20:</u></em> <strong>Arrival in India</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Finally today we will arrive India and our TOUR ENDS with HAPPY MEMORIES.</p>\r\n', '<p><em><u>Cost :</u></em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Rs.1,65,000/- + US$ 3450 = Rs.3,80,000/- Per Person on Twin Sharing</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Rs.1,65,000/- + US$ 3350 = Rs.3,73,700/- Per Person on Triple Sharing</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Rs.1,65,000/- + US$ 3000 = Rs.3,51,650/- Per Child (3 to 9 Years)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p align="center">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p align="center"><strong><em><u>If you Confirm before 20<sup>th</sup> Dec. 2013, following Discounts would apply</u></em></strong><br />\r\n<strong>4 Nights &amp; 5 Days Hong Kong &amp; Macau Package</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p align="center"><strong>(or)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p align="center"><strong>4 Nights &amp; 5 Days Dubai &amp; Abu Dhabi Package</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p align="center"><strong>(or)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p align="center"><strong>Cash Discount of Rs.30,000/- per Adult &amp; Rs.20,000/- per Child</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><u>Booking Terms</u></em></p>\r\n\r\n<p>To Confirm this booking, pls Send us the SCANNED COPY of ALL THE TRAVELING GUESTS (Pls see Minimum 6 Months Validity of Passport is required for any International Travel) to <a href="mailto:md@yougotrip.com">md@yougotrip.com</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>An Advance Payment of <strong>Rs.40,000/-</strong> (Non Refundable) in favour of <strong>&ldquo;MILK WHITE HOSPITALITY SERVICES INDIA PVT LTD&rdquo;</strong> payable at Coimbatore or Transfer to the below Bank Account.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p align="center">Account Name:&rdquo;<strong>MILK WHITE HOSPITALITY SERVICES INDIA PRIVATE LIMITED&rdquo;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><u>ICICI BANK DETAILS</u>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <u>CANARA BANK DETAILS</u>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Branch&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; :&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>Coimbatore Main Branch, Coimbatore&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong>Branch&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; :&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>HQ Road Branch, Coimbatore</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Account No&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; : &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>605305055238</strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&