rture of the tour; alternate options will be advised incase this happens.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><u>Important Note</u></em></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>All Group Tours would be conducted with Min 40 pax.&nbsp; If the Group size is below 30 pax means, the Guest would be transferred to the next available Group.&nbsp; If they want to go on the given dates means, it would be treated as SIC (Seat in Coach) basis with additional supplement cost.</li>\r\n	<li>We are not holding any confirmed seat in the flight and rooms. Flight seats and rooms are subject to availability.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '<p align="center"><strong><u>DAYWISE ITINERARY</u></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><u>Day 01</u></em><strong>:&nbsp;</strong>Arrival at Delhi Airport. From Airport&nbsp;and leave for&nbsp;Manali (550 Kms from Delhi)&nbsp;and&nbsp;<strong>Night Halt in the Coach. </strong><strong>(D)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><u>Day 02</u></em><strong>:&nbsp;</strong>Morning Breakfast enroute. On Arrival at Manali, Check in the Room (13.00 Hrs) &amp; Refresh yourself. Afternoon Visit Kulu Sightseeing &nbsp;(Pandoh Dam, Hanogi Mata Temple, 05 Minutes long Tunnel). Have Dinner in the Hotel &amp;&nbsp;<strong>Night Halt in Manali. </strong><strong>(B, L, &amp; D)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><u>Day 03</u></em><strong>:&nbsp;</strong>After Early Morning breakfast, leave for&nbsp;Rohtang Pass&nbsp;(Snow Point 50 Kms from Manali)&nbsp;and in the Afternoon leave for&nbsp;Manali Sight Seeing&nbsp;(Club House, Vashish Bath, Hadimba Temple, Tibeten Monastery)&nbsp;Evening free for&nbsp;Mall Road Shopping.&nbsp;Have Dinner &amp; Proceed to Amritstar &amp;&nbsp;<strong>Night Halt in Coach </strong><strong>(B, L, &amp; D)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\n<em><u>Day 04</u></em><strong>:&nbsp;</strong>Morning arrive Amritsar. Transfer to hotel. And After breakfast. Start your full day city tour with the blessings of Golden Temple-the most important sikh shrine which is also called Mecca for the Sikhs is a living symbol of the spiritual and historical traditions of the Sikhs.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Then visit Jallianwala Bagh- where, on April 13, 1919, British and Gurkha soldiers opened fire on an unarmed forbidden gathering, killing hundreds of civilians. After lunch visit Maharaja Ranjit Singh Summer Palace Museum- The summer place of Maharaja Ranjit Singh which is situated in the heart of Ram Bagh and later visit Indo-Pak Wagah Border to watch Flag Retreat Ceremony- Wagah, an army outpost on Indo-Pak border 30 Kms from Amritsar where the daily highlight is the evening &quot;Beating the Retreat&quot; ceremony. Soldiers from both countries march in perfect drill, going through the steps of bringing down their respective national flags. As the sun goes down, nationalistic fervour rises and lights are switched on marking the end of the day amidst thunderous applause. Return to hotel. Overnight stay in Amritsar. &amp;&nbsp;<strong>Night Halt in Amirstar. </strong><strong>(B, L, &amp; D)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><u>Day 05</u></em><strong>:&nbsp;</strong>After breakfast proceed to Delhi (450 Kms from Amirstar). On Arrival in Delhi Check in the Hotel &amp; Refresh Yourself. Evening is Free for Shopping. Have Dinner in the Hotel &amp;&nbsp;<strong>Night Halt in Delhi. </strong><strong>(B, L, &amp; D)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><u>Day 06</u></em><strong>:&nbsp;</strong>After breakfast Proceed to Full Day Delhi Sightseeing (Red Fort, Jama Masjid, Raj Ghat, Qutab Minar, Lotus Temple, President House, Parliament House, Indira Museum, India Gate, Birla Mandir))&nbsp;after that&nbsp;<strong>Evening free for Shopping in Karol Bagh / Sarojini Nagar Market. </strong>Have Dinner in the Hotel &amp;&nbsp;<strong>Night Halt in Delhi. </strong><strong>(B, L, &amp; D)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><u>Day 07</u></em><strong>:&nbsp;</strong>After Early Morning breakfast, for Agra (200 Kms from elhi)&nbsp;via&nbsp;Vrindavan (140 kms from Delhi)&nbsp;Sight Seeing&nb